# Markdown Document Tools

Tool for managing, merging and converting markdown files to HTML/PDF.

## Files

```
.
├── LICENSE
├── README.md
├── md-tools.sh          # Main script
├── manifest.yml         # Generated by script
├── styles.css          # Generated by script
├── complete.md         # Generated merged markdown
├── complete.html       # Generated HTML output
└── complete.pdf        # Generated PDF output
```

## Installation Requirements

```bash
# Install Homebrew (macOS)
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

# Install dependencies
brew install pandoc wkhtmltopdf
npm install -g @knennigtri/merge-markdown
```

## Usage

1. Clone repository:
```bash
git clone [repository-url]
cd [repository-name]
```

2. Make script executable:
```bash
chmod +x md-tools.sh
```

3. Run script:
```bash
./md-tools.sh
```

## Features

- Lists markdown files with their titles
- Auto-generates manifest for merging
- Merges multiple markdown files
- Converts to HTML with custom styling
- Converts to PDF with proper formatting

## Menu Options

1. List markdown files
2. Generate manifest
3. Merge files
4. Convert to HTML
5. Convert to PDF
6. Exit

